ax%20returns%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657a135f7a3c8094d5dcb122%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHunter%20Biden's%20tax%20returns%20reveal%20the%20details%20of%20his%20effort%20to%20settle%20up%20with%20the%20IRS%2C%20using%20millions%20of%20dollars%20borrowed%20from%20a%20friend.%20%3Cp%3EJulio%20Cortez%2FAP%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20reviewed%20hundreds%20of%20pages%20of%20Hunter%20Biden's%20financial%20records.%20The%20documents%20%E2%80%94%20made%20public%2C%20in%20part%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20today%20%E2%80%94%20include%20several%20years%20of%20personal%20tax%20returns%20filed%20by%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20son%20in%20the%20late%202010s%20and%20early%202020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHunter%20Biden's%202018%20individual%20tax%20return%2C%20also%20known%20as%20a%20Form%201040%2C%20offers%20an%20intimate%2C%20primary-source%20view%20of%20his%20income%20and%20his%20relationship%20with%20the%20IRS%2C%20subjects%20that%20are%20now%20the%20focus%20of%20a%20federal%20indictment.%20The%20view%20they%20give%20of%20Biden's%20lifestyle%20and%20his%20attitude%20toward%20his%20tax%20obligations%20is%20more%20nuanced%20than%20the%2056-page%20charging%20document%20released%20last%20week%20by%20Special%20Counsel%20David%20C.%20Weiss.%20That%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fsco-weiss%2Fpr%2Fgrand-jury-returns-indictment-charging-robert-hunter-biden-three-felony-tax-offenses%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520the%2520indictment%252C%2520Hunter%2Cwhen%2520he%2520filed%2520false%2520returns.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindictment%3C%2Fa%3E%20charged%20Biden%20with%20six%20misdemeanors%20spanning%20four%20tax%20years%2C%20and%20three%20felonies%20%E2%80%94%20including%20filing%20a%20false%20return%20and%20tax%20evasion%20%E2%80%94%20all%20from%202018.%20It%20sought%20to%20depict%20Biden%20in%20starkly%20moralistic%20terms%2C%20a%20debauched%20and%20entitled%20playboy%20who%20made%20his%20living%20off%20of%20sketchy%20influence-peddling%20deals%2C%20then%20spent%20it%20on%20sex%20workers%20and%20hotel%20rooms%20instead%20of%20paying%20his%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202018%20tax%20return%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%20and%20published%20exclusively%20on%20Thursday%20does%20not%20contradict%20that%20picture%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20offer%20any%20smoking-gun%20evidence%20of%20wrongdoing.%20But%20it%20does%20complicate%20the%20attempt%20by%20prosecutors%20to%20lay%20out%20a%20damning%20portrait%20of%20Biden%20as%20a%20consumer%20and%20taxpayer.%20The%20return%20shows%20what%20Hunter%20Biden%20did%20after%20hitting%20bottom%20during%20his%20years%20of%20addiction%20and%20profligate%20spending.%20By%20his%20own%20account%2C%20he%20spent%20much%20of%202017%20and%202018%20binging%20on%20crack%20cocaine%20and%20moving%20from%20hotel%20to%20hotel.%20Then%2C%20in%202019%2C%20he%20got%20sober%2C%20remarried%2C%20and%20found%20a%20wealthy%20friend%20to%20lean%20on%20%E2%80%94%20Los%20Angeles%20entertainment%20lawyer%20Kevin%20Morris.%20Morris%20lent%20Biden%20at%20least%20%244.6%20million%20as%20Biden%20tried%20to%20make%20things%20right%20with%20the%20IRS.%20Using%20Morris'%20money%2C%20Biden%20filed%20his%20overdue%20tax%20returns%20and%20voluntarily%20paid%20the%20IRS%20millions%20in%20back%20taxes%2C%20penalties%2C%20and%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeiss's%20investigation%20of%20Hunter%20Biden%20dates%20back%20to%202018.%20After%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F12%2F21%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fbarr-trump-hunter-biden-election.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20sparring%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20then-Attorney%20General%20Bill%20Barr%20and%20President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20it%20was%20ultimately%20Biden's%20attorney%20general%2C%20Merrick%20Garland%2C%20who%20did%20what%20Trump%20had%20long%20demanded%20and%20appointed%20Weiss%20as%20special%20counsel%20in%202023.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunter-biden-indicted-false-statements-gun-charges-sentence-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWeiss%20charged%20Biden%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20three%20federal%20gun%20charges%20in%20September%20after%20plea%20negotiations%20fell%20apart%3B%20Biden%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20in%20that%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20has%20not%20yet%20entered%20a%20plea%20on%20the%20new%20tax%20charges.%20%26quot%3BHe%20paid%20all%20of%20the%20taxes%20that%20are%20owed%20in%20this%20indictment%20more%20than%20two%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Abbe%20Lowell%2C%20who%20represents%20Biden%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2Fvideos%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2F12%2F09%2Fhunter-biden-attorney-tax-indictment-response-sot-src-vpx.cnn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BNobody%20in%20that%20position%20would%20be%20charged%20the%20way%20he%20was%20yesterday.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20Hunter%20Biden's%20legal%20team%20told%20BI%20by%20email%20that%20issues%20with%20the%202018%20tax%20return%20were%20%26quot%3Bsimple%20mistakes%2C%20not%20intentional%20misstatements.%26quot%3B%20They%20cited%20a%20letter%20from%20Lowell%20to%20the%20House%20Ways%20and%20Means%20Committee%20claiming%20that%20Biden%20had%20actually%20overstated%20his%20taxable%20income%20for%20that%20year%20and%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20due%20a%20refund.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20agree%20that%20it's%20unusual%20for%20the%20Justice%20Department%20to%20bring%20criminal%20charges%20in%20a%20case%20like%20this%2C%20where%20the%20old%20returns%20have%20been%20filed%2C%20the%20overdue%20taxes%20paid%2C%20and%20the%20only%20thing%20in%20dispute%20is%20the%20legality%20of%20business%20expenses%20claimed%20as%20deductions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20prosecutor%20who%20reviewed%20both%20the%20indictment%20and%20Hunter%20Biden's%202018%20tax%20return%20told%20BI%20that%20Biden's%20conduct%20falls%20short%20of%20what%20would%20typically%20prompt%20federal%20prosecutors%20to%20bring%20criminal%20charges.%20They%20requested%20anonymity%20because%20of%20the%20sensitivity%20of%20commenting%20on%20a%20pending%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20thousands%20of%20people%20who%20collectively%20owe%20the%20IRS%20billions%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20former%20prosecutor.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20prosecuting%20them%20criminally.%20We're%20meeting%20with%20them%20and%20trying%20to%20work%20out%20a%20payment%20schedule.%20Criminal%20charges%20under%20these%20kinds%20of%20circumstances%20are%20very%20unusual.%20I've%20never%20actually%20seen%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20what%20Hunter%20Biden%20wound%20up%20paying%20the%20IRS%2C%20broken%20down%20by%20year%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EFor%202016%2C%20Biden%20paid%20the%20IRS%20%24462%2C754%20in%20taxes%2C%2029%20percent%20of%20his%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EFor%202017%2C%20Biden%20paid%20the%20IRS%20%24710%2C598%20in%20taxes%2C%2030%20percent%20of%20his%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EFor%202018%2C%20Biden%20paid%20the%20IRS%20%24659%2C366%20in%20taxes%2C%2030%20percent%20of%20his%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%20self-reported%20income%20for%20these%20three%20years%20ranged%20between%20%241.5%20million%20and%20%242.1%20million%2C%20enough%20to%20put%20him%20in%20the%20top%20one%20percent%20of%20household%20earners.%20His%20effective%20tax%20rate%20was%20slightly%20higher%20than%20his%20fellow%20one-percenters.%20They%20paid%20the%20IRS%20an%20average%20of%2027%20percent%20of%20their%20household%20income%20as%20compared%20to%20Biden's%2029%20to%2030%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHunter%20Biden%20also%20paid%20more%20in%20tax%20over%20these%20three%20years%20than%20the%20%241.1%20million%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnytimes.com%2F2022%2F12%2F21%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-taxes-income.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%20did%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20four%20years%20of%20his%20presidency.%20Richard%20Nixon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.providencejournal.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2F2020%2F09%2F28%2Ffrom-journal-archives-nixonrsquos-income-tax-bill-1670-for-two-years%2F42698495%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%20a%20mere%20%241%2C670%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20a%20two-year%20span%20during%20his%20presidency%2C%20thanks%20mainly%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.taxnotes.com%2Ftax-history-project%2Ftax-history-did-irs-drop-ball-when-auditing-nixons-tax-returns%2F2023%2F05%2F26%2F7grtz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeductions%20that%20he%20took%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20donating%20his%20pre-presidential%20papers%20to%20the%20National%20Archives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20serious%20allegation%20laid%20out%20by%20Weiss%20is%20that%20Biden's%20stated%20income%20for%20one%20of%20those%20three%20years%2C%202018%2C%20is%20too%20low.%20According%20to%20the%20indictment%2C%20Biden%20wrongly%20labeled%20many%20transactions%20%E2%80%94%20luxury%20hotel%20rooms%2C%20payments%20to%20sex%20workers%2C%20%2430%2C000%20in%20college%20tuition%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0as%20business%20expenses.%20All%20of%20the%20three%20tax%20felonies%20that%20Biden%20is%20charged%20with%20originate%20with%20those%20allegedly%20fraudulent%20misclassifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20BI%20is%20publishing%20Biden's%20complete%202018%20tax%20return%2C%20a%20key%20document%20in%20the%20special%20counsel's%20criminal%20case%20alleging%20that%20in%20that%20same%20year%2C%20Biden%20underpaid%20his%20taxes%20and%20misreported%20some%20personal%20expenses%20as%20business%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20read%20in%20full%20here%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24223166-hunterbiden-1040-2018-binsider%2F%3Fembed%3D1%26responsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22HunterBiden-1040-2018-BInsider%20(Hosted%20by%20DocumentCloud)%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22914%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20referred%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20to%20Hunter%20Biden's%20representatives.%20Weiss's%20office%20at%20the%20Justice%20Department%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20also%20reviewed%20Biden's%20tax%20returns%20for%202016%20and%202017.%20All%20three%20years'%20filings%20show%20that%20as%20he%20descended%20into%20addiction%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20he%20effectively%20paid%20the%20IRS%20in%20advance%2C%20through%20withholdings%2C%20plummeted.%20The%20bulk%20of%20Biden's%20self-declared%20income%20shifted%20from%20wages%20paid%20out%20through%20Owasco%2C%20Biden's%20payroll%20company%2C%20to%20business%20income.%20A%20single%20line%20on%20the%20return%20%E2%80%94%20%241%2C956%2C694%20%E2%80%94%20notes%20what%20Biden%20reported%20he%20made%20from%20%26quot%3Blegal%20and%20consulting%20services.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20was%20not%20able%20to%20obtain%20access%20to%20other%20key%20documents%20supporting%20the%20felony%20charges%3A%20correspondence%20between%20Biden%20and%20his%20accountants%2C%20as%20well%20as%20tax%20filings%20for%20Owasco.%20The%20indictment%20alleges%20that%20Owasco%20received%20%26quot%3Bapproximately%20%242.1%20million%26quot%3B%20in%202018%20from%20a%20fund%20with%20ties%20to%20CEFC%20China%20Energy%20Co.%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20Chinese%20energy%20conglomerate.%26quot%3B%20But%20while%20the%20indictment%20is%20packed%20with%20details%20regarding%20Biden's%20overseas%20deals%2C%20the%20charges%20all%20stem%20from%20how%20he%20paid%20taxes%20on%20that%20money%2C%20not%20how%20he%20made%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20Owasco%20had%20gross%20receipts%20of%20%242%2C659%2C014%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23888014-memorandum-of-plea-agreement-exhibit-1-scrubbed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%20detailing%20a%20plea%20agreement%20between%20Biden's%20attorneys%20and%20prosecutors%20that%20collapsed%20in%20court.%20Only%20a%20tiny%20fraction%20of%20that%20money%2C%20%24159%2C000%2C%20appears%20on%20Biden's%201040%20return%20as%20wages.%20According%20to%20prosecutors%2C%20Biden%20later%20told%20his%20accountants%20that%20much%20of%20the%20remainder%20was%20used%20on%20business%20expenses%20that%20were%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20personal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Nassau%2C%20who%20teaches%20tax%20law%20at%20Syracuse%20University%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-67664144%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20criminal%20tax%20prosecutions%20are%20%26quot%3Bvery%20rare%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20amounts%20of%20money%20at%20issue%20in%20the%20indictment%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20potatoes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Holder%2C%20who%20led%20the%20Justice%20Department%20under%20President%20Barack%20Obama%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2Fvideos%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2F12%2F08%2Fhunter-biden-eric-holder-reaction-sot-lcl-vpx.cnn%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20believed%20political%20pressure%20was%20driving%20the%20tax%20charges.%20%26quot%3BI've%20spoken%20to%20former%20colleagues%2C%20both%20Republican%20and%20Democrat%2C%20who%20were%20United%20States%20attorneys%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20asked%20them%2C%20if%20you%20had%20these%20facts%20in%20your%20office%2C%20would%20you%20have%20brought%20this%20case%3F%20And%20the%20answer%2C%20to%20a%20person%2C%20was%20no.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20documents%20show%20that%20Biden%20did%20eventually%20get%20serious%20about%20making%20substantial%20(if%20late)%20payments%20to%20the%20IRS%2C%20they%20also%20show%20that%20the%20money%20Biden%20used%20to%20make%20them%20wasn't%20his%20own.%20It%20was%20borrowed%20from%20the%20man%20who%20has%20become%20his%20friend%2C%20confidante%2C%20and%20backer%2C%20Kevin%20Morris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorris%20is%20a%2060-year-old%20entertainment%20lawyer.%20He%20made%20tens%20of%20millions%20representing%20Matthew%20McConaughey%2C%20the%20creators%20of%20%26quot%3BSouth%20Park%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20as%20a%20producer%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Book%20of%20Mormon%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20hit%20musical.%20Morris%20and%20Biden%20reportedly%20met%20in%202019%20at%20a%20Democratic%20fundraiser.%20Since%20then%2C%20Morris%20has%20quarterbacked%20Biden's%20multi-pronged%20effort%20to%20fight%20back%20against%20House%20Republicans%20who%20are%20investigating%20him%2C%20an%20effort%20that%20includes%20civil%20lawsuits%2C%20responses%20to%20congressional%20subpoenas%2C%20and%20a%20reported%20documentary%20that%20will%20go%20on%20the%20counter-attack%20against%20Hunter%20Biden's%20GOP%20and%20MAGA-world%20adversaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%20that%20Morris%20%26quot%3Blent%20more%20than%20%242%20million%20to%20Hunter%20Biden%20which%20went%20to%20supporting%20his%20family%20and%20paying%20back%20taxes.%26quot%3B%20The%20indictment%20claims%20that%20Morris%2C%20who%20is%20identified%20only%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20entertainment%20lawyer%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BPersonal%20Friend%26quot%3B%20paid%20more%20than%20%241.2%20million%20to%20cover%20Biden's%20expenses%2C%20including%20rent%20payments%20on%20a%20lavish%20home%20in%20Malibu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%20own%20tax%20filings%20show%20that%20the%20support%20he%20received%20from%20Morris%20was%20far%20more%20substantial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kevin%20Morris%20reading%20a%20book.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657af81150edbc52a8641e9f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22705%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKevin%20Morris%2C%20an%20entertainment%20lawyer%2C%20has%20lent%20Hunter%20Biden%20at%20least%20%244.6%20million%2C%20according%20to%20Biden's%20tax%20returns.%3Cp%3EAlberto%20E.%20Rodriguez%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20according%20to%20Biden's%20tax%20return%2C%20Biden%20received%20%26quot%3Bfinancial%20support%20from%20a%20personal%20friend%20totaling%20approximately%20%241%2C425%2C000.%26quot%3B%20That%20support%20was%20formalized%20as%20a%20loan%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Ba%20promissory%20note%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20%241%2C417%2C634%20bearing%205%25%20interest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20according%20to%20Biden's%20tax%20return%2C%20Biden%20received%20another%20%243%2C240%2C355%20in%20financial%20support%2C%20which%20was%20also%20formalized%20as%20a%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20did%20not%20review%20Biden's%202022%20return%3B%20if%20Morris%20lent%20him%20money%20during%20that%20year%2C%20the%20amount%20is%20unknown.%20But%20the%20%244.6%20million%20documented%20by%20Biden's%202020%20and%202021%20returns%20is%20far%20more%20than%20Biden's%20past%20due%20tax%20liability%2C%20suggesting%20that%20Biden%20was%20living%20off%20funds%20borrowed%20from%20Morris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20person%20close%20to%20Morris%20said%20that%20beginning%20in%202020%2C%20Morris%20hired%20outside%20lawyers%20to%20vet%20and%20sign%20off%20on%20each%20of%20the%20loans%20that%20he%20made%20to%20Hunter%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20data%20show%20that%20Biden's%20reboot%20as%20a%20memoirist%20and%20fine%20artist%20did%20not%20produce%20taxable%20income%20on%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20millions%20he%20was%20making%20during%20his%20years%20as%20a%20Beltway%20lawyer%2C%20at%20least%20not%20during%20the%20first%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20according%20to%20Biden's%20tax%20return%2C%20he%20made%20%24187%2C500%20as%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BBeautiful%20Things%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20memoir%2C%20and%20another%20%2447%2C734%20from%20his%20career%20as%20an%20artist.%20All%20but%20%24134%20of%20the%20art%20income%20that%20year%20came%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20art%20to%20Kevin%20Morris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20according%20to%20Biden's%20tax%20return%2C%20he%20made%20%24374%2C759%20from%20his%20book%20and%20another%20%2483%2C250%20as%20an%20artist%2C%20%2412%2C649%20was%20deducted%20for%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunter-biden-joe-artwork-berges-gallery-elizabeth-hirsh-naftali-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20internal%20documents%20from%20Hunter%20Biden's%20gallerist%20showing%20that%20his%20artwork%20had%20grossed%20%241.3%20million.%20The%20bulk%20of%20Biden's%20share%20of%20that%20money%20%E2%80%94%2060%20percent%2C%20according%20to%20his%20contract%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0was%20likely%20paid%20out%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHunter%20Biden%20has%20long%20been%20the%20focus%20of%20obsessive%20and%20sometimes%20conspiratorial%20interest%20by%20Republicans%20in%20Congress%2C%20who%20used%20his%20overseas%20business%20dealings%20as%20part%20of%20the%20basis%20for%20opening%20a%20formal%20impeachment%20inquiry%20into%20Biden's%20father%2C%20in%20a%20party-line%20vote%20on%20Wednesday.%20The%20GOP%20fascination%20with%20Hunter%20Biden%20began%20with%20his%20lucrative%20service%20on%20the%20board%20of%20Burisma%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20energy%20company%2C%20and%20picked%20up%20steam%20just%20before%20the%202020%20election%2C%20when%20files%20purported%20to%20come%20from%20Biden's%20abandoned%20laptop%20were%20made%20public%20by%20Trump's%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GOP%20has%20never%20really%20let%20go%20of%20the%20idea%20that%20Hunter%20Biden%20can%20be%20used%20to%20weaken%20(if%20not%20take%20down)%20Joe%20Biden.%20Their%20inquiries%20have%20produced%20evidence%20that%20Hunter%20Biden%20traded%20on%20the%20family%20name%20and%20occasionally%20arranged%20for%20brief%