dinating%20between%20civil%20society%20members%2C%20Singh%20was%20in%20the%20thick%20of%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20spoke%20to%20Snigdhendu%20Bhattacharya%20over%20the%20phone%20after%20the%20summit%20ended%20with%20the%20formal%20adoption%20of%20the%20text%20of%20the%20Global%20Stock%20Take%2C%20an%20appraisal%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20climate%20action%2C%20and%20a%20future%20roadmap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBelow%20are%20the%20excerpts%20from%20the%20interview%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECOP28%20finally%20reached%20an%20agreement%20following%20intense%20and%20prolonged%20negotiations%2C%20overrunning%20the%20schedule.%20How%20would%20you%20describe%20the%20outcome%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFrom%20our%20perspective%2C%20the%20most%20crucial%20aspect%20was%20to%20secure%20the%20recognition%20that%20the%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20renewable%20energy%20must%20be%20just%20and%20equitable.%20This%20language%20has%20been%20accepted.%20Naturally%2C%20we%20demanded%20a%20much%20more%20robust%20wording%3A%20%E2%80%98fossil%20fuel%20phase-out%E2%80%99.%20Instead%2C%20we%20got%20the%20framing%20%E2%80%98transitioning%20away%E2%80%99.%20This%20is%20primarily%20due%20to%20strong%20resistance%20from%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20Even%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20were%20not%20entirely%20in%20favour%20of%20using%20stronger%20language%2C%20and%20it%20was%20actually%20they%20who%20proposed%20the%20%E2%80%98transitioning%20away%E2%80%99%20terminology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWould%20you%20consider%20the%20text%20a%20compromised%20one%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOverall%2C%20I%20would%20still%20call%20it%20historic.%20What%20we%20got%20is%20huge.%20The%20level%20of%20discussion%20leading%20up%20to%20and%20during%20the%20summit%2C%20which%20centered%20on%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20was%20unprecedented.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20the%20first%20time%20after%2030%20long%20years%20we%20have%20discussed%20fossil%20fuels%20so%20comprehensively.%20In%20COP26%2C%20we%20talked%20mostly%20about%20coal.%20It%20has%20become%20clear%20now%20that%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20just%20keep%20talking%20about%20emissions%2C%20we%20have%20to%20talk%20about%20moving%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20are%20disappointed%20with%20the%20way%20finance%20has%20been%20tackled.%20In%20some%20places%2C%20the%20language%20has%20actually%20been%20weakened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20major%20disappointments%20in%20this%20regard%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20references%20like%20%E2%80%9Crecognises%20the%20gap%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnotes%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Curges%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20they%20stop%20short%20of%20directly%20%E2%80%9Ccalling%E2%80%9D%20upon%20developed%20countries%20to%20fund%20the%20transition%2C%20or%20scale%20up%20adaptation%20finance.%20One%20excuse%20they%20have%20been%20using%20is%20that%20there%20is%20an%20ongoing%20process%20of%20New%20Collective%20Quantified%20Goal%20on%20Climate%20Finance%2C%20which%20has%20been%20kicked%20down%20the%20road.%20It%E2%80%99s%20set%20to%20be%20discussed%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20other%20loopholes%2C%20such%20as%20references%20to%20nuclear%20power%2C%20abatement%20and%20removal%20technologies%2C%20low%20carbon%20hydrogen%20and%20carbon%20capture%20and%20storage%20(CCS)%20systems.%20Some%20of%20these%20things%20can%20act%20as%20loopholes%20and%20prolong%20the%20use%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20We%20know%20that%20these%20technologies%20are%20unreliable%20and%20the%20claims%20they%20make%20are%20untrue.%20Nuclear%20is%20a%20risky%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x147.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x502.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689104%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22588%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECOP28%20summit%20in%20Dubai.%20Photo%3A%20Screengrab%20via%20X%2F%40COP28_UAE%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20seem%20to%20be%20some%20last-minute%20changes%20that%20happened%20after%20releasing%20the%20GST%20draft%20on%20December%2011.%20One%20of%20them%20is%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20provision%20of%20%E2%80%9Climitation%E2%80%9D%20on%20new%20coal%20facilities.%20What%20transpired%20at%20the%20venue%20after%20the%20draft%20was%20released%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20my%20discussions%20with%20countries%20heavily%20reliant%20on%20coal%2C%20like%20Pakistan%2C%20it%20was%20evident%20they%20were%20greatly%20concerned.%20Right%20from%20the%20day%20the%20conversation%20around%20fossil%20fuels%20started%20in%202021%20with%20COP26%2C%20and%20going%20on%20in%20G7%20and%20G20%20meetings%2C%20countries%20who%20only%20have%20coal%20as%20a%20major%20source%20of%20energy%20are%20facing%20the%20unfair%20demand%20of%20limiting%20the%20use%20or%20moving%20away%20from%20it%20without%20any%20assurance%20of%20finance%20and%20technology.%20This%20is%20all%20the%20more%20so%20when%20the%20rich%20countries%20have%20been%20expanding%20oil%20and%20gas%20in%20their%20backyard.%20The%20US%20is%20now%20the%20largest%20fossil%20fuel%20producer%20and%20has%20the%20loudest%20voice%20in%20seeking%20an%20end%20to%20coal%20use.%20This%20is%20hypocrisy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20global%20fossil%20fuel%20expansion%20plan%2C%20for%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20the%20five%20countries%20that%20have%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20share%20of%20that%20expansion%20are%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Australia%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20Norway.%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpriceofoil.org%2F2023%2F09%2F12%2Fplanet-wreckers-how-20-countries-oil-and-gas-extraction-plans-risk-locking-in-climate-chaos%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHome-%2CPlanet%2520Wreckers%253A%2520How%2520Countries%2527%2520Oil%2520and%2520Gas%2520Extraction%2520Plans%2CRisk%2520Locking%2520in%2520Climate%2520Chaos%26amp%3Btext%3DOnly%252020%2520countries%252C%2520led%2520overwhelmingly%2Cplanned%2520between%25202023%2520and%25202050.%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20Oil%20Change%20International%2C%20titled%20%3Cem%3EPlanet%20Wreckers%3A%20How%20Countries%E2%80%99%20Oil%20and%20Gas%20Extraction%20Plans%20Risk%20Locking%20in%20Climate%20Chaos%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Rich%20countries%20are%20going%20on%20with%20such%20expansion%20plans%20and%20imposing%20limitations%20on%20coal%2C%20which%20is%20crucial%20for%20countries%20like%20India%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20China%20and%20Indonesia.%20So%2C%20there%20was%20a%20pushback%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20the%20language%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-ends-historic-but-also-disappointing-experts%5C%22%3ECOP28%20Draws%20to%20a%20Close%2C%2023%20Hours%20Overtime%3A%20Historic%20but%20Also%20Disappointing%2C%20Say%20Experts%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoesn%E2%80%99t%20coal%20really%20have%20many%20adverse%20impacts%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20course%2C%20as%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20I%20would%20like%20to%20see%20coal%20phased%20out%20as%20early%20as%20possible%2C%20not%20just%20because%20of%20the%20climate%20goals%20but%20because%20of%20the%20adverse%20impacts%20of%20coal%20extraction%20such%20as%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20local%20environment%20and%20displacement.%20Coal%20is%20not%20something%20we%20should%20rely%20on.%20However%2C%20from%20a%20global%20climate%20justice%20perspective%2C%20the%20initial%20draft%20would%20have%20indeed%20been%20unfair%20to%20developing%20countries%20like%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20divide%20between%20the%20global%20north%20and%20the%20global%20south%20appeared%20quite%20sharp.%20Could%20you%20describe%20the%20situation%20at%20the%20summit%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20divide%20has%20always%20been%20there%2C%20but%20it%20is%20becoming%20much%20starker%20because%20rich%20countries%20are%20only%20paying%20lip%20service%20than%20any%20real%20action%20and%20they%20have%20also%20resisted%20providing%20finance%20and%20technology.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%2C%20this%20time%20developing%20countries%20were%20stronger%20in%20their%20argument%20that%20we%20need%20to%20tackle%20all%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20a%20just%2C%20orderly%2C%20and%20equitable%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20coal%20versus%20oil%20debate%20has%20been%20going%20on%20for%20quite%20a%20few%20years.%20Two%20years%20ago%2C%20coal%20was%20formally%20included%20in%20the%20text%20but%20oil%20and%20gas%20never%20appeared%20in%20it.%20This%20time%2C%20even%20though%20fossil%20fuel%20has%20found%20a%20mention%2C%20there%20is%20no%20explicit%20mention%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20except%20for%20referring%20to%20gas%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98transitional%20fuel.%E2%80%99%20How%20did%20the%20negotiations%20unfold%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20was%20a%20power%20game.%20Rich%20countries%20first%20created%20a%20narrative%20that%20we%20have%20to%20phase%20out%20coal%20because%20it%20is%20highly%20polluting.%20There%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20if%20you%20compare%20coal%2C%20oil%2C%20and%20gas%2C%20coal%20is%20the%20most%20polluting%2C%20followed%20by%20oil%20and%20gas.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20expansion%20plan%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20globally%2C%20they%20are%20far%20far%20more%20than%20coal.%20Even%20though%20coal%20is%20more%20polluting%20as%20a%20fossil%20fuel%2C%20the%20global%20expansion%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%20is%20far%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20developed%20countries%20have%20actually%20done%20most%20of%20the%20industrial%20burning%20of%20coal.%20Oil%20came%20much%20later.%20Now%20that%20they%20are%20dependent%20on%20oil%2C%20they%20want%20to%20demonise%20coal%20and%20countries%20dependent%20on%20it.%20They%20are%20smart.%20They%20know%20how%20to%20do%20diplomacy%20and%20how%20to%20build%20a%20narrative.%20They%20got%20the%20agenda%20in%20the%20G7%20and%20G20%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20has%20been%20the%20role%20of%20India%20in%20this%20entire%20debate%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIndia%20was%20pushing%20for%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20language%20%E2%80%98all%20fossil%20fuel%E2%80%99%20at%20COP26.%20However%2C%20somehow%2C%20the%20statement%20that%20it%20made%20in%20public%20regarding%20%E2%80%9Cphase-down%E2%80%9D%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%9Cphase-out%E2%80%9D%20did%20not%20help%20India%20in%20arguing%20its%20case.%20But%20what%20it%20did%2C%20in%20hindsight%2C%20is%20that%20people%20started%20looking%20at%20those%20issues%20in%20more%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ECivil%20society%20played%20a%20very%20important%20role%20in%20exposing%20the%20US%20and%20all%20other%20oil%20and%20gas%20producer%20countries%2C%20in%20insisting%20that%20you%20cannot%20just%20talk%20about%20one%20fossil%20fuel.%20We%20did%20not%20gain%20much%20traction%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20COP27.%20But%20the%20public%20campaigning%20that%20we%20have%20been%20doing%20has%20been%20very%20helpful%20in%20landing%20all%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20the%20text%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20you%20notice%20the%20formation%20of%20any%20global%20south%20solidarity%20or%20have%20they%20remained%20divided%20over%20their%20own%20interests%20and%20priorities%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20was%20a%20general%20consensus.%20Obviously%2C%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Pacific%20Island%20states%20and%20the%20least%20developed%20countries%2C%20who%20are%20suffering%20the%20most%2C%20were%20putting%20more%20pressure%20on%20large%20countries%20to%20move%20away%20from%20all%20fossil%20fuels.%20They%20wanted%20action%20from%20all%20polluters%2C%20particularly%20the%20G20%20countries.%20A%20just%20and%20equitable%20transition%20was%20more%20important%20for%20countries%20like%20Indonesia%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20and%20India.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20small%20island%20states%20and%20the%20least%20developed%20countries%20are%20also%20realising%20that%20if%20equity%20is%20not%20applied%2C%20the%20transition%20will%20never%20really%20happen%20as%20fast%20as%20it%20is%20needed%2C%20and%20they%20will%20suffer%20more.%20This%20realisation%20fostered%20a%20sense%20of%20overall%20unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20the%20mitigation%20versus%20adaptation%20debate%20play%20out%3F%20The%20rich%20countries%20have%20always%20tended%20to%20attach%20lesser%20priority%20to%20adaptation.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ERich%20countries%20were%20never%20concerned%20about%20adaptation.%20If%20we%20had%20left%20it%20to%20them%2C%20the%20Paris%20Agreements%20would%20not%20have%20found%20any%20mention%20of%20adaptation%2C%20or%20loss%20and%20damage%20for%20that%20matter.%20Adaptation%20is%20very%20important%20for%20developing%20countries%2C%20as%20they%20are%20already%20facing%20impacts%20and%20not%20getting%20enough%20support.%20For%20them%2C%20prioritising%20adaptation%20is%20quite%20natural.%20Rich%20countries%20have%20often%20pitted%20these%20issues%20against%20each%20other.%20When%20they%20want%20developing%20countries%20to%20move%20forward%2C%20they%20argue%20for%20a%20greater%20focus%20on%20mitigation.%20This%20dynamic%20was%20also%20evident%20at%20this%20summit.%20The%20text%20of%20the%20Global%20Goal%20on%20Adaptation%20was%20being%20traded%20against%20the%20mitigation%20text%2C%20or%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20text.%20Eventually%2C%20we%20got%20through%20both%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20this%20was%20a%20win%20for%20the%20developing%20and%20the%20least%20developed%20countries%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhat%20we%20need%20to%20recognise%20is%20that%20it%20is%20all%20part%20of%20the%20same%20continuum.%20If%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20reduce%20emissions%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20have%20to%20spend%20more%20money%20on%20adaptation%2C%20and%20if%20you%20fail%20to%20do%20adaptation%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20have%20to%20suffer%20more%20loss%20and%20damage.%20Significantly%2C%20adaptation%20is%20now%20important%20for%20the%20rich%20countries%20as%20well.%20The%20impacts%20are%20increasing.%20What%20they%20have%20to%20understand%20is%20that%20the%20developing%20countries%20need%20more%20support%20but%20the%20issue%20affects%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20that%20the%20goals%20have%20been%20set%2C%20what%20should%20be%20India%E2%80%99s%20priorities%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWe%20already%20got%20a%20direction%20of%C2%A0what%C2%A0we%20need%20to%20do%20%E2%80%93%20we%20need%20to%20move%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%20What%20we%20did%20not%20have%20a%20direction%20for%20is%C2%A0how%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20how%20it%20is%20going%20to%20happen%20in%20a%20just%20and%20equitable%20manner.%20We%20have%20now%20come%20to%20the%C2%A0how%C2%A0part.%20We%2C%20as%20climate%20justice%20movements%2C%20have%20been%20advocating%20for%20a%20Fossil%20Fuel%20Non-Proliferation%20Treaty%20that%20should%20deal%20with%20the%C2%A0how%C2%A0part.%20If%20we%20look%20at%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20and%20the%20kind%20of%20discussions%20we%20had%20and%20the%20time%20it%20took%20to%20reach%20this%20language%2C%20detailed%20discussion%20and%20framework%20are%20necessary%20for%20us%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWe%20need%20a%20new%20global%20framework%20dealing%20with%20how%20we%20stop%20explorations%20and%20expansions%20and%20how%20we%20support%20the%20workers%20while%20phasing%20out.%20How%20do%20we%20do%20it%2C%20who%20does%20it%2C%20and%20when.%20We%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20%E2%80%98just%2C%20orderly%20and%20equitable%E2%80%99%20means%20in%20practical%20terms.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20think%20India%20should%20join%20countries%20like%20Columbia%20which%20has%20recently%20called%20for%20a%20Fossil%20Fuel%20Non-Proliferation%20Treaty%20to%20be%20negotiated.%20That%20kind%20of%20framework%20would%20be%20really%20helpful%20for%20India%20to%20secure%20international%20cooperation%20for%20a%20just%20transition%20to%20non-fossil%20fuel-based%20energy%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702557610000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14174858%2FEffect-30.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewir