%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fputin-is-taking-questions-from-ordinary-russians-along-with-journalists-as-his-reelection-bid-begins%2Famp_articleshow%2F105989501.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%3A%20Russia%20can't%20exist%20without%20sovereignty%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702546439000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FF54A%2Fproduction%2F_132049726_p0gzg602.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67714359%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20president%20vows%20to%20strengthen%20Russia's%20sovereignty%20as%20he%20starts%20a%20lengthy%20press%20conference.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fworld-europe-67714359%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kashmir%20Line%20of%20Control-Set%20War%20Film%20%E2%80%98The%20Collaborator%E2%80%99%20Wraps%20Production%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702546200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2FThe-Collaborator.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235837631%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Production%20has%20wrapped%20on%20the%20wartime%20coming-of-age%20feature%20film%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Collaborator%2C%E2%80%9D%20based%20on%20the%20international%20bestseller%20by%20Kashmiri%20novelist%20Mirza%20Waheed.%20The%20story%20is%20set%20in%20the%201990s%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%20of%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20that%20separates%20Indian%20Kashmir%20from%20Pakistani%20Kashmir.%20The%2017-year%20old%20protagonist%20known%20only%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CBoy%E2%80%9D%20is%20forced%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Naman%20Ramachandran%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fkashmir-line-of-control-war-film-the-collaborator-india-pakistan-1235837631%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fkashmir-line-of-control-war-film-the-collaborator-india-pakistan-1235837631%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fkashmir-line-of-control-war-film-the-collaborator-india-pakistan-1235837631%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Art%2C%20Architecture%20and%20Design%20Biennale%3A%20The%20Fine%20Line%20Between%20Government%20Support%20and%20Politicisation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14121410%2FH20231208146124.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20great%20things%20about%20art%20has%20always%20been%20the%20impossibility%20of%20a%20logical%20definition.%20A%20dead%20butterfly%20was%20as%20much%20art%2C%20as%20it%20was%20a%20biological%20phenomenon%3B%20a%20pear%20was%20a%20nutritious%20fruit%20and%20also%20a%20delicate%20still-life%20painting.%20When%20art%20loses%20these%20multiple%20meanings%2C%20it%20drops%20a%20few%20notches%20from%20philosophy%20to%20science%20to%20mere%20data%2C%20thereby%20also%20losing%20the%20essential%20element%20of%20redundancy%20that%20keeps%20it%20alive%20and%20well%20and%20kicking.%20When%20governments%20enter%20the%20fray%2C%20art%20begins%20to%20flounder%20further.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20week%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1985002%5C%22%3Einauguration%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20India%20Art%20Architecture%20and%20Design%20Biennale%20(IAADB)%20at%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Red%20Fort%20set%20off%20alarm%20bells%20amongst%20several%20artists%20and%20writers.%20An%20official%20endorsement%20by%20the%20government%20of%20what%20constitutes%20Indian%20art%20and%20design%20is%20not%20just%20troubling%20from%20the%20standpoint%20of%20its%20content%2C%20but%20also%20for%20the%20fact%20that%20art%20should%20be%20so%20brazenly%20claimed%20by%20the%20government.%20It%20has%20taken%20many%20decades%20to%20establish%20a%20notable%20independence%20from%20political%20patronage%2C%20but%20this%20official%20government%20support%20%E2%80%93%20and%20its%20ready%20acceptance%20by%20many%20artists%20and%20supposedly%20autonomous%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20comes%20as%20a%20surprise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20to%20say%20that%20government%20funds%20are%20not%20required%20for%20the%20arts%2C%20but%20it%20does%20stand%20to%20reason%20that%20bureaucratic%20support%20and%20money%20should%20ideally%20go%20where%20most%20needed.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1794907%5C%22%3EAtmanirbhar%20Bharat%20Centre%3C%2Fa%3E%20established%20in%20support%20of%20traditional%20artists%20and%20crafts%20is%20a%20commendable%20recent%20initiative%20to%20keep%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20crafts%20alive%2C%20especially%20so%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20elite%20arts%20of%20painting%2C%20sculpture%2C%20installation%2C%20etc.%2C%20are%20now%20either%20wholly%20international%20or%20receive%20enough%20support%20from%20private%20galleries%20and%20foundations.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20revival%20of%20dying%20practices%20and%20struggling%20folk%20traditions%20is%20a%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction%3B%20the%20politicisation%20of%20art%2C%20however%2C%20is%20an%20altogether%20different%20matter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECertainly%2C%20Biennales%20in%20Venice%2C%20Singapore%20and%20Dubai%20all%20receive%20city%20and%20federal%20support%2C%20but%20they%20are%20run%20as%20autonomous%20private%20events%2C%20without%20bureaucracy%20or%20government%20presence.%20Even%20national%20museums%20and%20galleries%20in%20the%20US%20which%20get%20federal%20funding%20remain%20independent%20and%20entirely%20free%20to%20select%20and%20showcase%20art.%20In%20the%201980s%2C%20when%20the%20Gallery%20of%20American%20Art%20placed%20a%20burger%20stand%20and%20McDonald%E2%80%99s%20arches%20in%20an%20exhibition%20on%20ordinary%20American%20vernacular%20architecture%2C%20it%20was%20done%20without%20a%20government%20banner%20overhanging%20the%20exhibit.%20The%20show%20raised%20a%20lot%20of%20eyebrows%20and%20asked%20questions%20about%20the%20relevance%20of%20such%20banal%20buildings%20inside%20a%20gallery%3B%20but%20nowhere%20was%20the%20exhibit%20derided%20as%20a%20waste%20of%20cultural%20resources.%20Would%20our%20National%20Gallery%20of%20Modern%20Art%20consider%20placing%20a%202BHK%20builder%20flat%20in%20its%20main%20hall%20to%20draw%20attention%20to%20the%20state%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20architecture%3F%20Or%20would%20the%20IGNCA%20spend%20its%20budget%20on%20a%20display%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20mall%20buildings%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20Biennale%20exhibition%20does%20attempt%20to%20be%20broad-based%20by%20including%20works%20by%20some%20unknown%20artists%20in%20new%20mediums%2C%20its%20overall%20historical%20and%20cultural%20stance%20overshadows%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20more%20secular%20and%20inclusive%20perspective%20on%20art.%20While%20calling%20the%20show%20a%20celebration%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20art%2C%20architecture%20and%20design%2C%20its%20real%20intent%20it%20seems%20is%20to%20primarily%20showcase%20craft%20and%20promote%20the%20idea%20that%20valuable%20Indian%20art%20comes%20from%20a%20collective%20discipline%2C%20an%20effort%20directed%20towards%20the%20development%20of%20the%20country%20%E2%80%93%20like%20stone%20carvers%20chiselling%20the%20panel%20of%20a%20temple%2C%20or%20bronze%20casters%20working%20on%20a%20religious%20statue.%20Doubtless%2C%20Indian%20temples%2C%20gardens%2C%20traditional%20doors%20and%20%3Cem%3Ebaolis%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20exhibit%20are%20a%20source%20of%20enormous%20cultural%20pride%2C%20and%20their%20inclusion%20in%20the%20show%20highlights%20the%20painstaking%20manner%20in%20which%20these%20architectural%20elements%20were%20constructed%20and%20crafted.%20But%20to%20call%20them%20all%20works%20of%20art%20wrongly%20presumes%20that%20everything%20accomplished%20before%20the%20British%20occupation%20had%20great%20artistic%20merit.%20Though%20finely%20crafted%2C%20many%20Rajasthani%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehaveli%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20doors%20and%20palace%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echattris%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20were%20inherently%20unattractive%2C%20even%20ugly%3B%20many%20gardens%20and%20temples%20don%E2%80%99t%20qualify%20for%20inclusion%20for%20the%20same%20reason.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20real%20problem%20of%20course%20remains%20with%20the%20sponsorship%20itself.%20However%20well-intentioned%20the%20government%2C%20the%20visible%20face%20behind%20art%20will%20always%20be%20suspect.%20Few%20federal%20governments%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world%20make%20so%20brazen%20a%20representation%20of%20themselves.%20Sadly%20when%20the%20Indian%20government%20gives%20money%20for%20art%2C%20it%20wants%20the%20public%20to%20not%20only%20know%2C%20but%20it%20must%20also%20select%20the%20work%20and%20showcase%20it%20under%20the%20umbrella%20of%20its%20own%20institutions.%20The%20Lalit%20Kala%20Academy%2C%20the%20Council%20of%20Architecture%2C%20the%20National%20Gallery%20of%20Modern%20Art%2C%20and%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20are%20of%20course%20independent%20entities%2C%20with%20their%20independent%20voices.%20However%2C%20their%20artistic%20message%20is%20not%20%E2%80%93%20and%20should%20not%20be%20%E2%80%93%20in%20bureaucratic%20control.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20casual%20indifference%20to%20art%E2%80%99s%20complex%20reasoning%2C%20value%20and%20presentation%2C%20needs%20funding%20support%20that%20leaves%20the%20art%20and%20the%20artist%20alone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%20with%20so%20robust%20a%20showing%20for%20art%20at%20the%20Biennale%2C%20the%20government%20may%20opt%20for%20ventures%20into%20other%20arts.%20Soon%20enough%20there%20may%20be%20national%20events%20in%20stand-up%20comedy%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Great%20Indian%20Comedy%20Show%20%E2%80%93%20with%20jokes%20written%20and%20vetted%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Education%2C%20and%20another%20for%20theatre%20and%20films.%20With%20an%20audience%20so%20large%2C%20dispersed%20and%20mixed%20it%20may%20be%20good%20to%20know%20what%20is%20art%2C%20what%20is%20humour%2C%20and%20what%2C%20a%20good%20story.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fgautambhatiaarch%5C%22%3EGautam%20Bhatia%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20architect%20and%20sculptor.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702546159000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14121410%2FH20231208146124.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fart-architecture-design-biennale-government-support-politicisation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20official%20endorsement%20by%20the%20government%20of%20what%20constitutes%20Indian%20art%20and%20design%20is%20not%20just%20troubling%20from%20the%20standpoint%20of%20its%20content%2C%20but%20also%20for%20the%20fact%20that%20art%20should%20be%20so%20brazenly%20claimed%20by%20the%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fart-architecture-design-biennale-government-support-politicisation%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%203rd%20H-1B%20lottery%3A%20What%20does%20this%20mean%20for%20techies%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702545902000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105989212%2Cimgsize-27166.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fnri%2Fthere-will-be-no-third-h-1b-cap-lottery-for-the-year-ending-september-30-2