0of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Froad-deaths-down-by-5-globally-indias-share-rise%2Farticleshow%2F105956424.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20report%20suggests%20that%20efforts%20to%20improve%20road%20safety%20are%20making%20progress%20but%20fall%20short%20of%20meeting%20the%20UN%20Decade%20of%20Action%20for%20Road%20Safety%202021%E2%80%932030%20target%20to%20halve%20deaths%20by%202030.%20Road%20traffic%20deaths%20and%20injuries%20remain%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Froad-deaths-down-by-5-globally-indias-share-rise%2Farticleshow%2F105956424.cms%5C%22%3Eleading%20cause%20of%20death%20for%20individuals%20aged%205-29%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Froad-deaths-down-by-5-globally-indias-share-rise%2Farticleshow%2F105956424.cms%5C%22%3Eyears%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%2012th%20leading%20cause%20of%20death%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVulnerable%20road%20users%2C%20including%20pedestrians%2C%20cyclists%2C%20and%20motorcyclists%2C%20account%20for%20over%2050%25%20of%20global%20fatalities%2C%20with%20occupants%20of%204-wheel%20vehicles%20contributing%20to%20one-third.%20The%20report%20emphasises%20the%20need%20for%20better%20infrastructure%2C%20stating%20that%20nearly%2080%25%20of%20all%20assessed%20roads%20do%20not%20meet%20a%20minimum%203-star%20rating%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Froad-deaths-down-by-5-globally-indias-share-rise%2Farticleshow%2F105956424.cms%5C%22%3Epedestrian%20safety%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELow-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20face%20the%20highest%20risk%2C%20with%2092%25%20of%20global%20deaths%20occurring%20in%20these%20nations.%20Regionally%2C%2028%25%20of%20all%20fatalities%20occur%20in%20the%20WHO%20South-East%20Asia%20Region%2C%2025%25%20in%20the%20Western%20Pacific%20Region%2C%2019%25%20in%20the%20African%20Region%2C%2012%25%20in%20the%20Region%20of%20the%20Americas%2C%2011%25%20in%20the%20Eastern%20Mediterranean%20Region%2C%20and%205%25%20in%20the%20European%20Region%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Froad-deaths-down-by-5-globally-indias-share-rise%2Farticleshow%2F105956424.cms%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20European%20region%20reported%20the%20most%20significant%20drop%20in%20deaths%20since%202010%2C%20at%2036%25%2C%20attributed%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Csafe%20system%20approach.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Western%20Pacific%20and%20South-East%20Asia%20regions%20reported%20declines%20of%2016%25%20and%202%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReductions%20in%20deaths%20were%20observed%20in%20108%20countries.%20Notably%2C%20ten%20countries%E2%80%94Belarus%2C%20Brunei%20Darussalam%2C%20Denmark%2C%20Japan%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20Norway%2C%20Russian%20Federation%2C%20Trinidad%20and%20Tobago%2C%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20and%20Venezuela%E2%80%94successfully%20achieved%20the%20target%20reduction%20of%20at%20least%2050%25%20in%20their%20fatality%20numbers.%20However%2C%2066%20countries%2C%20including%2028%20in%20the%20African%20region%2C%20experienced%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20deaths%20since%202010%2C%20the%20WHO%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Froad-deaths-down-by-5-globally-indias-share-rise%2Farticleshow%2F105956424.cms%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702538432000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14114640%2FScreenshot-2023-12-14-at-11.45.46-AM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fglobal-road-deaths-drop-5-indias-record-worsens-who-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20share%20in%20global%20road%20fatalities%20rose%20from%2011%25%20to%2013%25%2C%20with%20number%20of%20deaths%20increasing%20from%201.34%20lakh%20in%2