n%20the%20former%E2%80%99s%20borrowing%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fkerala-govt-files-suit-against-centre-in-supreme-court-for-imposing-limits-on-the-states-borrowing-capacity-244427%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20original%20suit%20was%20filed%20under%20Article%20131%20of%20the%20constitution%20which%20gives%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20original%20jurisdiction%20to%20settle%20disputes%20between%20a%20state%20government%20and%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kerala%20government%20has%20said%20that%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20lower%20its%20borrowing%20capacity%20will%20push%20it%20to%20grave%20financial%20crisis.%20Such%20borrowings%20are%20regulated%20by%20the%20Kerala%20Fiscal%20Responsibility%20Act%2C%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20has%20thus%20challenged%20letters%20issued%20by%20the%20Union%20finance%20ministry%20on%20March%2027%20and%20August%2011%2C%20along%20with%20the%20amendments%20made%20to%20Section%204%20of%20the%20Fiscal%20Responsibility%20and%20Budget%20Management%20Act%2C%202003%20through%20the%20Finance%20Act%2C%202018%2C%20noting%20that%20it%20meddles%20with%20the%20Kerala%20government%E2%80%99s%20rights%20to%20borrow%20from%20available%20sources%2C%20including%20open%20market%20borrowings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kerala%20government%20has%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20further%20curtailed%20its%20borrowing%20powers%20by%20pushing%20under%20the%20%E2%80%9Cborrowings%E2%80%9D%20definitions%20actions%20which%20are%20not%20seen%20as%20such%20by%20the%20Article%20293%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kerala%20government%20has%20posited%20in%20its%20suit%20that%20around%20Rs%2026%2C000%20crores%20is%20imminently%20and%20urgently%20required%20for%20it%20to%20avert%20an%C2%A0%20impending%20financial%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20abi