28%20deal%20to%20'transition%20away'%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20actually%20mean%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702489200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-cop28-ahmed-al-jaber_6391547.jpg%3F20231213075729%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhat-does-the-cop28-deal-to-transition-away-from-fossil-fuels-actually-mean-13029353%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20UN%20climate%20change%20conference%20in%20Dubai%20has%20seen%20almost%20200%20countries%20commit%20to%20%26quot%3Btransitioning%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20first%20time.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A87%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhat-does-the-cop28-deal-to-transition-away-from-fossil-fuels-actually-mean-13029353%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhat-does-the-cop28-deal-to-transition-away-from-fossil-fuels-actually-mean-13029353%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhat-does-the-cop28-deal-to-transition-away-from-fossil-fuels-actually-mean-13029353%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22COP28%20Draws%20to%20a%20Close%2C%2023%20Hours%20Overtime%3A%20Historic%20but%20Also%20Disappointing%2C%20Say%20Experts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20COP28%20drew%20to%20a%20close%20on%20December%2013%2C%20almost%20a%20day%20after%20schedule%2C%20some%20called%20the%20conference%20%E2%80%9Chistoric%E2%80%9D.%20For%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20history%20of%20COPs%2C%20the%20outcome%20document%20of%20the%20first%20Global%20Stocktake%20at%20COP28%20called%20for%20parties%20to%20transition%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20a%20just%20and%20equitable%20way.%20The%20COP%20also%20witnessed%20parties%20adopting%20the%20framework%20for%20the%20Global%20Goal%20on%20Adaptation%20and%20other%20outcomes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20first%20Global%20Stocktake%20also%20absolves%20developed%20countries%20from%20several%20responsibilities%20including%20transitioning%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20including%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20which%20are%20also%20polluting%20resources%2C%20as%20well%20as%20providing%20time-bound%20climate%20finance%2C%20several%20excerpts%20commented.%20Similarly%2C%20recommending%20the%20use%20of%20carbon%20capture%20utilisation%20and%20storage%20technologies%20to%20balance%20emissions%20hangs%20like%20a%20dark%20cloud%20over%20COP28%2C%20for%20these%20are%20technologies%20that%20science%20still%20does%20not%20prove%20will%20work%2C%20scientists%20have%20held.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Historic%E2%80%99%20for%20call%20to%20transition%20from%20fossil%20fuels%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20day%20of%20COP28%2C%20November%2030%2C%20witnessed%20the%20operationalisation%20of%20the%20loss%20and%20damage%20fund%20for%20developing%20countries%20and%20all%20nations%20vulnerable%20to%20climate%20change.%20The%20last%20day%20of%20COP28%2C%20however%2C%20dragged%20on%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-licypriya-kangujam-global-stocktake%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eno%20consensus%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20regarding%20a%20draft%20text%20of%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20first%20Global%20Stocktake%2C%20as%20well%20as%20several%20other%20documents%20such%20as%20the%20Global%20Goal%20on%20Adaptation%20and%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENegotiations%20carried%20on%20into%20the%20night%20of%20December%2012%2C%20the%20last%20official%20day%20of%20COP28%2C%20and%20well%20into%20the%20early%20morning%20of%20December%2013.%20Finally%2C%20the%20COP28%20presidency%20uploaded%20the%20latest%20%E2%80%93%20and%20final%20%E2%80%93%20text%20on%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fdocuments%2F636608%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eoutcome%20of%20the%20first%20Global%20Stocktake%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20December%2013.%20On%20the%20evening%20of%20December%2013%20at%205%3A11%20pm%20UAE%20time%2C%20and%2023%20hours%20into%20overtime%2C%20COP28%20president%20Sultan%20Al-Jaber%20brought%20the%20gavel%20down%20on%20the%20conference%20and%20the%20consensus%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20outcome%20document%20of%20the%20Global%20Stocktake%2C%20a%20framework%20for%20the%20Global%20Goal%20on%20Adaptation%20and%20several%20other%20outcomes%20%E2%80%94%20to%20a%20standing%20ovation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThe%20moment%20history%20was%20made.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%81%B0Everyone%20came%20together%20from%20day%20one.%20Everyone%20united%2C%20everyone%20acted%20and%20everyone%20delivered.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FKYsRN6Bu4K%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FKYsRN6Bu4K%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20COP28%20UAE%20(%40COP28_UAE)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCOP28_UAE%2Fstatus%2F1734837123260285266%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2013%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECOP28%20was%20historic%20in%20that%20transitioning%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20found%20mention%20in%20the%20outcome%20document.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20conference%20%E2%80%9Cfurther%20recognises%20the%20need%20for%20deep%2C%20rapid%20and%20sustained%20reductions%20in%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20in%20line%20with%201.5%20%C2%B0C%20pathways%20and%20calls%20on%20Parties%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20following%20global%20efforts%2C%20in%20a%20nationally%20determined%20manner%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20and%20their%20different%20national%20circumstances%2C%20pathways%20and%20approaches..%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20approaches%20include%20tripling%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%20globally%20and%20doubling%20the%20global%20average%20annual%20rate%20of%20energy%20efficiency%20improvements%20by%202030%3B%20moving%20towards%20phasing%20down%20unabated%20coal%20(however%2C%20there%20is%20no%20mention%20of%20oil%20or%20gas%2C%20which%20are%20also%20polluting%20fossil%20fuels)%3B%20%E2%80%9Csubstantially%20reducing%E2%80%9D%20non-carbon-dioxide%20emissions%20globally%2C%20especially%20methane%2C%20by%202030%3B%20quickly%20phasing%20out%20inefficient%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20that%20do%20not%20address%20energy%20poverty%20or%20just%20transitions%3B%20taking%20action%20towards%20achieving%20net%20zero%20emission%20energy%20systems%20worldwide%20and%20utilising%20zero-%20and%20low-carbon%20fuels%20well%20before%20or%20by%20around%202050%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20approaches%20that%20the%20outcome%20document%20also%20calls%20for%20is%20%E2%80%9Ctransitioning%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20energy%20systems%2C%20in%20a%20just%2C%20orderly%20and%20equitable%20manner%2C%20accelerating%20action%20in%20this%20critical%20decade%2C%20so%20as%20to%20achieve%20net%20zero%20by%202050%20in%20keeping%20with%20the%20science%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CCOP28%20occurred%20at%20a%20decisive%20moment%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20climate%20change.%20It%E2%80%99s%20important%20that%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20Global%20Stocktake%20clearly%20reaffirms%20the%20need%20for%20limiting%20global%20temperature%20rise%20to%201.5%C2%B0C%20%26amp%3B%20that%20this%20requires%20drastic%20reductions%20in%20emissions%20in%20this%20decade.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20there%20is%20a%20recognition%20of%20the%20need%20to%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20%E2%80%93%20after%20many%20years%20in%20which%20the%20discussion%20of%20this%20issue%20was%20blocked%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fantonioguterres%2Fstatus%2F1734836109425758248%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%2C%20secretary%20general%20of%20the%20UN.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUNEP%20executive%20director%20Inger%20Andersen%20also%20commented%20that%20%E2%80%9CCOP28%20has%20delivered%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20at%20climate%20talks%2C%20a%20clear%20call%20on%20countries%20to%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20deal%20is%20not%20perfect%2C%20but%20one%20thing%20is%20clear%3A%20the%20world%20is%20no%20longer%20denying%20our%20harmful%20addiction%20to%20fossil%20fuels%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%E2%80%9CNow%20we%20move%20beyond%20bargaining%20to%20action.%20As%20the%20Secretary-General%20has%20said%2C%20the%20phase-out%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20is%20inevitable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20called%20it%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbeginning%20of%20the%20end%20for%20fossil%20fuels%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThis%20COP%20will%20mark%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20end%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20text%20we%20have%20in%20front%20of%20us%20sets%20in%20motion%20an%20irreversible%2C%20and%20accelerated%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarks%20by%20Commissioner%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FWBHoekstra%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40WBHoekstra%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FCOP28%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23COP28%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FCWeam2qlnM%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FCWeam2qlnM%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20European%20Commission%20(%40EU_Commission)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FEU_Commission%2Fstatus%2F1734860489400692884%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2013%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECOP28%20will%20be%20seen%20as%20one%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20historic%20COPs%E2%80%9D%2C%20commented%20Avinash%20Persaud%2C%20emeritus%20professor%2C%20Gresham%20College%20and%20Special%20Envoy%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20Barbados%20on%20Investment%20and%20Financial%20Services.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20operationalised%20a%20loss%20and%20damage%20fund%2C%20recapitalised%20the%20Green%20Climate%20Fund%20and%20orchestrated%20an%20international%20climate%20finance%20system%20that%20prepares%20for%20new%20levies%20alongside%20emboldened%20development%20banks%20and%20new%20private%20sector%20flows.%20Today%2C%20we%20have%20committed%20to%20triple%20renewable%20investments%20and%20have%20a%20just%20transition%20from%20fossil%20fuels%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20some%20activists%20were%20disappointed%20that%20an%20immediate%20fossil%20fuel%20phase-out%20didn%E2%80%99t%20work%20out%2C%20such%20a%20move%20would%20have%20either%20%E2%80%9Chit%20developing%20countries%20hardest%20or%20been%20meaningless%E2%80%9D%20without%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctrade%2C%20investment%20and%20finance%20to%20achieve%20it%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndeed%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20stand%20has%20been%20clear%20across%20several%20COPS%20%E2%80%93%20that%20a%20sudden%20phase-out%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20will%20cripple%20the%20economy%20and%20its%20people%2C%20and%20that%20a%20phase-down%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20and%20taking%20into%20account%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccommon%20but%20differentiated%20responsibilities%E2%80%9D%20based%20on%20national%20circumstances%20must%20be%20adopted%20by%20developing%20countries%20like%20India.%20The%20country%20has%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-licypriya-kangujam-global-stocktake%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eput%20the%20onus%20on%20developed%20countries%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20fund%20climate%20finance%20to%20tackle%20adaptation%20and%20mitigation%20actions%20in%20least-developed%20and%20developing%20countries%2C%20as%20well%20as%20countries%20that%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20climate%20change.%20India%20has%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fdeveloping-nations-should-be-given-fair-share-of-global-carbon-budget-pm-modi-at-cop28%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecalled%20for%20developing%20nations%20to%20be%20given%20a%20fair%20share%20of%20the%20carbon%20budget%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20since%20developed%20countries%20have%20already%20eaten%20into%20a%20huge%20share%20of%20it%2C%20leaving%20very%20little%20for%20developing%20countries%20to%20consume%20to%20lift%20their%20people%20out%20of%20poverty.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EToday%2C%20the%20world%20came%20together%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FCOP28%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23COP28%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Dubai%2C%20UAE%20to%20display%20positive%20collaboration%20and%20camaraderie%20for%20an%20action-oriented%20approach%20towards%20a%20greener%20and%20healthier%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20its%20G20%20Presidency%20steered%20by%20PM%20Shri%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnarendramodi%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40narendramodi%3C%2Fa%3E%20ji%2C%20India%20displayed%20the%20resolve%20to%20make%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FeC07BAr4Fy%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FeC07BAr4Fy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Bhupender%20Yadav%20(%40byadavbjp)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fbyadavbjp%2Fstatus%2F1734873454288273492%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2013%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%A6and%20still%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdisappointing%E2%80%9D%2C%20say%20many%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHarjeet%20Singh%2C%20head%20(global%20political%20strategy)%20at%20Climate%20Action%20Network%20International%2C%20said%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Clong-overdue%20direction%20to%20move%20away%20from%20coal%2C%20oil%2C%20and%20gas%20has%20been%20set%E2%80%9D%20at%20COP28.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CYet%2C%20the%20resolution%20is%20marred%20by%20loopholes%20that%20offer%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20industry%20numerous%20escape%20routes%2C%20relying%20on%20unproven%2C%20unsafe%20technologies%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20unproven%20and%20unsafe%20technologies%20he%20referred%20to%20include%20carbon%20capture%20and%20utilisation%20and%20storage%20(CCUS)%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20store%20emissions%20from%20large%20polluting%20sources%20by%20means%20such%20as%20injecting%20them%20into%20deep%20geological%20formations.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20a%20highly%20controversial%20technique%20for%20carbon%20removal%2C%20for%20scientists%20say%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20yet%20that%20CCUS%20can%20help%20lower%20emissions.%20In%20fact%2C%20a%20recent%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimateanalytics.org%2Fpublications%2Funabated-the-carbon-capture-and-storage-86-billion-tonne-carbon-bomb-aimed-at-derailing-a-fossil-phase-out%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20released%20by%20international%20think%20tank%20Climate%20Analytics%20on%20December%205%20found%20that%20relying%20on%20carbon%20capture%20and%20storage%20could%20release%20an%20extra%2086%20billion%20tonnes%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20between%202020%20and%202050.%20These%20technologies%2C%20however%2C%20are%20among%20the%20approaches%20that%20the%20outcome%20document%20of%20the%20Global%20Stocktake%20at%20COP28%20recommends%20that%20countries%20invest%20in%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAccelerating%20zero-%20and%20low-emission%20technologies%2C%20including%2C%20inter%20alia%2C%20renewables%2C%20nuclear%2C%20abatement%20and%20removal%20technologies%20such%20as%20carbon%20capture%20and%20utilisation%20and%20storage%2C%20particularly%20in%20hard-to-abate%20sectors%2C%20and%20low-carbon%20hydrogen%20production%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hypocrisy%20of%20wealthy%20nations%2C%20particularly%20the%20US%2C%20as%20they%20continue%20to%20expand%20fossil%20fuel%20operations%20massively%20while%20merely%20paying%20lip%20service%20to%20the%20green%20transition%2C%20stands%20exposed%2C%E2%80%9D%20commented%20Singh.%20%E2%80%9CDeveloping%20countries%2C%20still%20dependent%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20for%20energy%2C%20income%2C%20and%20jobs%2C%20are%20left%20without%20robust%20guarantees%20for%20adequate%20financial%20support%20in%20their%20urgent%20and%20equitable%20transition%20to%20renewable%20energy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20majority%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20power%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20comes%20from%20coal-based%20power%20plants.%20While%20India%20has%20been%20transitioning%20to%20solar%20and%20wind%20power.%20It%20has%20added%20around%20100%20GW%20of%20installed%20electric%20capacity%2C%20of%20which%20around%2080%25%20is%20attributed%20to%20non-fossil%20fuel-based%20resources%2C%20between%202017%20and%202023%2C%20Indian%20Union%20environment%20minister%20Bhupender%20Yadav%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1984434%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20while%20delivering%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20statement%20at%20COP28.%20Such%20transitions%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20%E2%80%93%20that%20COP28%20has%20called%20for%20in%20its%20outcome%20document%20%E2%80%93%20however%2C%20hugely%20impinges%20on%20the%20Nationally%20Determined%20Contributions%20that%20each%20nation%20submits%20to%20the%20UN%20voluntarily.%20More%20finances%20for%20the%20transition%20as%20well%20as%20for%20technology%20transfer%20will%20help%20developing%20countries%20achieve%20the%20transition%20faster.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAbsolving%20developed%20countries%20from%20several%20responsibilities%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20COP28%20recognised%20the%20immense%20financial%20shortfall%20in%20tackling%20climate%20impacts%2C%20the%20final%20outcomes%20fall%20disappointingly%20short%20of%20compelling%20wealthy%20nations%20to%20fulfill%20their%20financial%20responsibilities%20%E2%80%93%20obligations%20amounting%20to%20hundreds%20of%20billions%2C%20which%20remain%20unfulfilled%2C%E2%80%9D%20Singh%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDeveloped%20countries%20have%20pledged%20more%20than%20US%24%20650%20million%20for%20the%20loss%20and%20damage%20fund%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20impacts%20caused%20by%20climate%20change%20in%20developing%20countries%20and%20nations%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20climate%20change.%20However%2C%20the%20outcome%20document%20of%20the%20Global%20Stocktake%20does%20not%20mention%20anything%20about%20developed%20countries%20phasing%20out%20their%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20such%20as%20oil%20and%20gas%20%E2%80%93%20which%20are%20also%20polluting.%20Per%20the%20document%2C%20it%20%E2%80%9Crecognises%20that%20transitional%20fuels%20can%20play%20a%20role%20in%20facilitating%20the%20energy%20transition%20while%20ensuring%20energy%20security%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20an%20Indian%20perspective%2C%20this%20text%20displays%20greater%20parity%20between%20coal%20and%20other%20fossil%20fuels%20but%20it%20appears%20to%20absolve%20developed%20countries%20of%20the%20responsibility%20of%20phasing%20out%20their%20fossil%20fuel%20use%20%E2%80%9Cin%20this%20critical%20decade%E2%80%9D%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ulka%20Kelkar%2C%20executive%20director%2C%20Climate%2C%20World%20Resources%20Institute%20India.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20the%20reference%20to%20%E2%80%98transitional%20fuels%E2%80%99%20explicitly%20gives%20gas%20producing%20countries%20the%20license%20to%20sell%20more%20gas%20rather%20than%20invest%20in%20renewable%20energy.%20It%20also%20exonerates%20the%20developed%20countries%20from%20making%20up%20the%20finance%20gap%20so%20far%2C%20though%20it%20recognises%20that%20the%20gap%20in%20adaptation%20finance%20is%20%E2%80%98widening%E2%80%99%20and%20that%20doubling%20the%20current%20low%20levels%20of%20adaptation%20finance%20will%20be%20insufficient.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20real%20winners%20of%20the%20new%20draft%20text%20are%20the%20fossil%20producers%20that%20continue%20to%20term%20%E2%80%98gas%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20transitional%20fuel%2C%E2%80%9D%20commented%20Vibhuti%20Garg%2C%20director%2C%20South%20Asia%2C%20IEEFA.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20only%20positive%20in%20the%20new%20draft%20text%20is%20the%20removal%20of%20%E2%80%98optionality%E2%80%99%20in%20regards%20to%20tripling%20renewable%20energy%20targets%20and%20doubling%20of%20energy%20efficiency.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EClimate%20finance%20from%20developed%20countries%20still%20lagging%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdisappointing%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20outcome%20document%20has%20not%20recognised%20the%20need%20for%20developed%20countries%20to%20provide%20the%20financial%20support%20needed%20for%20developing%20countries%20in%20transitioning%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20to%20meet%20their%20adaptation%20needs%2C%20including%20for%20the%20Loss%20and%20Damage%20Fund%2C%20commented%20Meena%20Raman%2C%20head%20of%20programmes%2C%20Third%20World%20Network%2C%20an%20independent%20non-profit%20international%20research%20and%20advocacy%20organisation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CInstead%2C%20we%20see%20escape%20routes%20being%20set%20in%20place%20across%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20decisions%20to%20dilute%20their%20commitments%20and%20divert%20attention%20to%20the%20private%20sector%20and%20the%20multilateral%20development%20banks%20for%20the%20provision%20of%20climate%20finance%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raman%20added.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20highly%20regrettable.%20Scaled-up%20ambition%20on%20finance%20is%20much%20needed%20to%20secure%20the%20high%20ambition%20in%20developing%20countries.%20Otherwise%2C%20any%20lofty%20global%20targets%20will%20only%20remain%20a%20pipe%20dream.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20COP28%20shows%20that%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cappetite%E2%80%9D%20for%20climate%20action%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%20%E2%80%9Cmoved%20significantly%20forward%2C%20its%20willingness%20to%20pay%20lags%20behind%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20activist%20Teresa%20Anderson%2C%20global%20lead%20on%20climate%20justice%2C%20ActionAid%20International.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20mission%20to%20move%20to%20a%20fossil-free%20future%20does%20not%20yet%20have%20the%20finance%20components%20needed%20to%20make%20this%20goal%20workable%20for%20lower-income%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20rich%20countries%20had%20been%20willing%20to%20put%20real%20finance%20and%20fair%20timelines%20on%20the%20table%2C%20the%20outcome%20could%20have%20been%20much%20stronger.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16171651%2FFypRzGmXoAA7M1T-e1686916210159.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16171651%2FFypRzGmXoAA7M1T-e1686916210159.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16171651%2FFypRzGmXoAA7M1T-e1686916210159-300x158.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F16171651%2FFypRzGmXoAA7M1T-e1686916210159-1024x538.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-658605%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EActivists%20press%20for%20just%20transition%20at%20Bonn%2C%20Germany.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40fossiltreaty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMoving%20towards%20a%20north-south%20divide%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECOP28%20has%20%E2%80%9Clargely%20disappointed%20on%20all%20fronts%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Arunabha%20Ghosh%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20Council%20on%20Energy%2C%20Environment%20and%20Water%20(CEEW).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20sufficiently%20raised%20climate%20ambition%2C%20held%20historical%20polluters%20accountable%2C%20or%20established%20effective%20mechanisms%20to%20finance%20climate%20resilience%20and%20a%20just%20low-carbon%20transition%20for%20the%20Global%20South%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20operationalisation%20of%20the%20Loss%20and%20Damage%20fund%20on%20the%20first%20day%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20noteworthy%20success%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9Csubsequent%20developments%20revealed%20a%20discordant%20trajectory%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Global%20Stocktake%E2%80%99s%20final%20text%20lacked%20the%20candid%20acknowledgement%20of%20problems%20and%20the%20teeth%20required%20to%20fight%20them.%20The%20exclusive%20focus%20on%20rapidly%20phasing%20down%20unabated%20coal%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20all%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20heightens%20the%20risk%20of%20exacerbating%20the%20North-South%20global%20divide.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECOP28%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20instate%20effective%20financial%20mechanisms%2C%20obliging%20historical%20emitters%20to%20contribute%2C%20jeopardises%20support%20for%20developing%20nations%20in%20meeting%20their%20Nationally%20Determined%20Contributions%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20urgency%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%20demands%20immediate%20reforms%20be%20made%20to%20the%20COP%20process%20to%20ensure%20that%20accountability%2C%20implementation%2C%20and%20climate%20justice%20become%20central%20to%20all%20efforts.%20Otherwise%2C%20future%20COPs%20risk%20becoming%20obsolete.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702487478000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-ends-historic-but-also-disappointing-experts%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20transitioning%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20found%20place%20in%20the%20consensus%20of%20parties%20but%20developed%20countries%20have%20once%20again%20wriggled%20out%20of%20several%20aspects%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0including%20delivering%20on%20time-bound%20climate%20finance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-ends-historic-but-also-disappointing-experts%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi's%20BJP%20Has%20Confirmed%20Nehru's%20Worries%20About%20the%20Jana%20Sangh's%20Divisive%20Plans%20for%20Kashmir%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F07%2FNehru.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20speaking%20in%20Calcutta%20(now%20Kolkata)%20on%20January%201%2C%201952%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20prime%20minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20stated%20that%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20(J%26amp%3BK)%E2%80%99s%20accession%20to%20India%20was%20made%20possible%20because%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20region%2C%20led%20by%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%2C%20were%20fascinated%20by%20the%20secular%20aspects%20of%20our%20struggle%20for%20independence%20and%20rejected%20Mohammad%20Ali%20Jinnah%E2%80%99s%20two-nation%20theory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Nehru%20was%20constrained%20to%20say%20that%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%2C%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20and%20the%20Praja%20Parishad%20of%20Jammu%20used%20abusive%20language%20against%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20and%20wanted%20the%20restoration%20of%20Hari%20Singh%20as%20maharaja%20of%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20asserted%20in%20that%20speech%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20see%20that%20there%20can%20be%20no%20greater%20vindication%20than%20this%20of%20our%20secular%20policies%2C%20our%20Constitution%2C%20that%20we%20have%20drawn%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20towards%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20just%20imagine%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20remarked%20with%20apprehension%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhat%20would%20have%20happened%20in%20Kashmir%20if%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%20or%20any%20other%20communal%20party%20had%20been%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20affairs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENehru%E2%80%99s%20apprehensions%20fructified%20by%20the%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%E2%80%99s%20far-sighted%20observation%20of%20Kashmir%20chillingly%20played%20out%20when%20in%20August%202019%2C%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%E2%80%99s%20successor%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20was%20%E2%80%9Cat%20the%20helm%20of%20affairs%E2%80%9D%20and%20its%20leader%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20by%20virtue%20of%20being%20prime%20minister%20of%20India%20with%20a%20huge%20majority%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20controlled%20the%20entire%20state%20apparatus%20and%20unilaterally%20downgraded%20J%26amp%3BK%20from%20a%20full-fledged%20state%20to%20a%20Union%20territory%20(UT)%20while%20also%20doing%20away%20with%20its%20special%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20people%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20suffered%20from%20a%20huge%20democratic%20deficit%20for%20no%20fault%20of%20their%20own%20and%20confronted%20several%20harsh%20measures%2C%20including%20prolonged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fjammu-and-kashmir-4g-internet-costs%5C%22%3EInternet%3C%2Fa%3E%20bans%20and%20a%20clampdown%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fjk-delimitation-over-2-voter-revisions-done-but-elections-nowhere-in-sight%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20processes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20without%20which%20they%20remained%20unrepresented%20at%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20their%C2%A0government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fends-matter-not-the-means-decoding-scs-approval-for-reading-down-of-article-370%5C%22%3EEnds%20Matter%2C%20Not%20the%20Means%3A%20Decoding%20SC%E2%80%99s%20Approval%20for%20Reading%20Down%20of%20Article%20370%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENehru%20linked%20the%20Babri%20mosque%20issue%20with%20Kashmir%20in%201950%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20quite%20coincidental%20that%20on%20the%20intervening%20night%20of%20December%2022-23%2C%201949%2C%20two%20idols%20%E2%80%93%20Lord%20Ram%20and%20Sita%20%E2%80%93%20were%20surreptitiously%20placed%20under%20the%20central%20dome%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20Nehru%20expressed%20his%20anxiety%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20United%20Provinces%20(now%20Uttar%20Pradesh)%20that%20this%20development%C2%A0could%20affect%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20letter%20he%20wrote%20on%20February%205%2C%201950%2C%20to%20G.B.%20Pant%2C%20Nehru%20categorically%20stated%20that%20the%20developments%20concerning%20the%20idols%E2%80%99%20secret%20placement%20would%20spell%20serious%20consequences%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20and%20gravely%20impact%20the%20Kashmir%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worthwhile%20to%20reproduce%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20exact%20words%20from%20that%20letter.%20He%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20shall%20be%20glad%20if%20you%20will%20keep%20me%20informed%20of%20the%20Ayodhya%20situation.%20As%20you%20know%2C%20I%20attached%20great%20importance%20to%20it%20and%20to%20its%20repercussions%20on%20all-India%20affairs%20and%20more%20especially%20Kashmir.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20remarks%20by%20Nehru%20brought%20out%20his%20sensitivity%20in%20understanding%2C%20in%201950%20itself%2C%20that%20the%20placement%20of%20those%20idols%20inside%20the%20Babri%20mosque%20would%20exacerbate%20communal%20problems%20so%20severely%20that%20the%20secular%20fabric%20of%20our%20country%20would%20be%20torn%20apart%2C%20and%20the%20democratic%20processes%20set%20in%20motion%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20after%20it%20joined%20the%20Indian%20Union%20would%20be%20badly%20vitiated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fears%20expressed%20by%20Nehru%20about%20Jana%20Sangh%E2%80%99s%20unfavourable%20disposal%20towards%20J%26amp%3BK%20have%20been%20materialised%20by%20the%20Modi-led%20BJP%20regime.%20Apart%20from%20scrapping%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20special%20status%20in%C2%A0August%202019%20and%20downgrading%20it%20to%20a%20UT%2C%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-ram-temple-ayodhya-foundation-stone%5C%22%3Elaid%20the%20foundation%20brick%20for%20a%20Ram%20temple%3C%2Fa%3E%20almost%20exactly%20a%20year%20later%20at%20the%20same%20place%20where%20the%20Babri%20mosque%20was%20illegally%20demolished%2C%20following%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgement%20permitting%20the%20temple%E2%80%99s%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fayodhyatimeline%5C%22%3EAyodhya%3A%20Once%20There%20Was%20a%20Mosque%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20remarkable%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20gave%20the%20land%20to%20those%20who%20demolished%20the%20Babri%20mosque%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20Ram%20temple%20in%20the%20same%20place%20where%20that%20mosque%20once%20stood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20apex%20court%2C%20in%20another%20remarkable%20turn%20of%20events%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-kashmir-article-370-verdict%5C%22%3Eapproved%20the%20abrogation%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20special%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20evaded%20adjudicating%20the%20issue%20of%20its%20reduction%20to%20a%20UT%20even%20as%20it%20upheld%20the%20UT%20status%20of%20Ladakh%2C%20one%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20erstwhile%20constituent%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJ%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20status%20was%20downgraded%20to%20a%20UT%20by%20the%20Modi%20regime%20while%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20was%20imposed%20%E2%80%93%20because%20the%20politically%20appointed%20governor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fplan-for-grand-coalition-in-jk-prompts-governor-to-dissolve-assembly%5C%22%3Edissolved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20state%20assembly%20in%20November%202018.%20This%20raises%20the%20concern%20that%20what%20was%20done%20to%20J%26amp%3BK%20can%20be%20done%20to%20any%20other%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20prospect%20is%20worrisome%20as%20far%20as%20federalism%20is%20concerned.%20The%20overwhelming%20sway%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20tinkering%20with%20the%20statehood%20of%20a%20federal%20unit%20has%20grave%20implications%20for%20the%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20192340%2FH20220424111143.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20192340%2FH20220424111143.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20192340%2FH20220424111143-300x154.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20192340%2FH20220424111143-1024x525.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-641296%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22615%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20J%26amp%3BK%20LG%20Manoj%20Sinha%20at%20an%20exhibition%20in%20Samba%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20on%20April%2024%2C%202022.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDemocratic%20deficit%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20assembly%20was%20dissolved%20in%20November%202018%2C%20elections%20have%20so%20far%20not%20been%20conducted%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%20It%20has%20troubled%20all%20those%20who%20believed%20in%20our%20constitutional%20scheme%20of%20governance%2C%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20which%20is%20a%20federal%20framework%20and%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20upholding%20the%20revocation%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20special%20status%20under%20Article%20370%2C%20even%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FLU%2Farticle_370.pdf%5C%22%3Eelections%20to%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20legislative%20assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20be%20completed%20before%20September%2030%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENever%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20India%20has%20any%20Union%20government%20downgraded%20a%20state%20to%20a%20UT%20as%20was%20unilaterally%20done%20in%20the%20case%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20which%20has%20serious%20implications%20for%20its%20identity%20and%20democratic%20credentials%20as%20an%20organic%20component%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fjammu-and-kashmir-ladakh-union-territory%5C%22%3EHistorically%2C%20UTs%20Become%20States.%20Now%20the%20Centre%20Is%20Reversing%20That%20Trend%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worthwhile%20to%20note%20that%20even%20at%20the%20time%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20accession%20to%20the%20Indian%20Union%20in%20October%201947%20in%20the%20face%20of%20an%20invasion%C2%A0by%20Pakistan-backed%20Pashtun%20tribesmen%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20making%20it%20a%20part%20of%20that%20country%2C%20Nehru%20never%20contemplated%20making%20it%20a%20UT%20and%20ensuring%20direct%20rule%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20it%20is%20rather%20shocking%20that%20those%20who%20vociferously%20claimed%20that%20the%20abrogation%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20status%20would%20end%20all%20forms%20of%20terrorism%20there%20and%20bring%20it%20all-round%20progress%20have%20failed%20to%20restore%20its%20statehood%20even%20four%20years%20after%20it%20was%20downgraded%20to%20a%20UT%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20ensure%20elections%20and%20the%20large-scale%20participation%20of%20its%20people%20in%20its%20representative%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20even%20MPs%20and%20several%20others%20%E2%80%93%20be%20they%20journalists%20or%20civil%20society%20representatives%20%E2%80%93%20who%20took%20a%20critical%20stand%20against%20direct%20rule%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20were%20subjected%20to%20coercive%20measures%2C%20incarceration%20and%20prolonged%20harassment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20long-drawn-out%20internet%20clampdown%20in%20the%20whole%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20very%20gravely%20impaired%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20rights%20and%20liberties%20to%20communicate.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fright-to-access-to-internet-a-fundamental-right-sc-on-jk-restrictions-6209407%2F%5C%22%3Einterpreted%20the%20right%20to%20access%20the%20internet%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20so%20in%20shutting%20it%20down%2C%20the%20regime%20there%20grossly%20infringed%20upon%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20its%20accession%20to%20the%20Indian%20Union%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir%20never%20suffered%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20deprivation%20of%20their%20democratic%20rights%2C%20which%20were%20affirmed%20by%20establishing%20a%20representative%20government%20in%20place%20of%20its%20monarchy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20telling%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20conduct%20elections%20for%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20state%20assembly.%20It%20represents%20a%20sorry%20state%20of%20affairs%20that%20Nehru%20apprehended%20J%26amp%3BK%20would%20be%20reduced%20to%20in%20case%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%20controlled%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERid%20India%20of%20the%20communal%20virus%20by%20learning%20from%20Kashmir%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20making%20a%20statement%20in%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20(legislative)%20on%20March%205%2C%201948%2C%20Nehru%20categorically%20stated%20that%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20issue%20is%20not%20an%20issue%20of%20communalism%2C%20and%20that%20the%20rest%20of%20India%20should%20learn%20from%20it%20the%20lessons%20of%20communal%20harmony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20India%2C%20currently%20embroiled%20in%20a%20majoritarian%20narrative%2C%20save%20itself%20from%20a%20communal%20imbroglio%20by%20defending%20the%20secular%20and%20composite%20ethos%20of%20Kashmir%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fs-n-sahu%5C%22%3ES.N.%20Sahu%3C%2Fa%3E%20served%20as%20an%20officer%20on%20special%20duty%20to%20President%20K.R.%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702484131000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F07%2FNehr